<HEADLINE> Sun Awarded July's Asian Player of Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 26 (Xinhua) -- China's Sun Jihai was
awarded the Asian Player of the Month for July by the Asian
Football Confederation.
</P>
<P>
Sun was now with English side Crystal Palace on loan from the
Chinese first division side Dalian Wanda.
</P>
<P>
Waiting for the final nod from Britain's labor authority, the
23-year-old full-back scored in Wanda's 3-1 victory over Qingdao
Hainiu last weekend, extending Wanda's margin over the
second-placed Shanghai Shenhua to 11 points with seven rounds
left this season.
</P>
<P>
The Coach of the Month Award goes to Iranian former goalie
Nasr Hejazi, who becomes the second Iranian in row to win the
trophy.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's Samawira Basri wins The Goal of the Month on a
goal in a S-League match between Jurong and Tanjong Pagar, where
Pagar won 2-1.
</P>
<P>
July's Team of the Month award was won by Japan's J-League
side Shimizu S-Pulse, which is coached by Argentine Ossic
Ardiles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
