<HEADLINE> Annan Recommends UN Role in Legislative Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 26 (Xinhua) -- U.N Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Wednesday submitted to the Security Council
recommendations on a possible role of the United Nations in the
planned legislative elections in the Central African Republic.
</P>
<P>
The recommendations are contained in his report on the United
Nations Mission in Central African Republic (MINURCA).
</P>
<P>
The proposed operational plan for MINURCA includes the
logistical support of electoral material and equipment, the
observation of legislative elections and security of electoral
materials and observers.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General urged all parties in the country to fully
assume their responsibilities in the elections and to participate
in them in a manner that would strengthen the democratic process
and contribute to genuine national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
In the report, Annan also provided an update on electoral
developments in the country since his last report of June 19,
1998. He pointed out that President Ange-Felix Patasse had taken
a number of decisions in preparations for the elections
including the establishment of the Electoral Commission.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council is holding discussions on the report
Wednesday morning.  
</P>
</TEXT>
