<HEADLINE> Ethiopia and U.S. Company Sign Mines Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Mines and Energy announced that the ministry signed on Wednesday
here an exploration agreement with Abay Natural Resources
Development PLC whose major share holder is Abay Resources
Technology International PLC of America.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the ministry said, the agreement
gives the licensee an exclusive right to explore for opal
mineral, a semi-precious gemstone, for the coming three years.
</P>
