north Shoa area, Amhara region, covers 94.75 square kilometers.
</P>
<P>
During the agreed period the licensee will spend a minimum of
1,329,765 Birr (187,290 US dollars) and is expected to commence
the exploration activity within 60 days from the signing of the
agreement, the release added.
</P>
<P>
There are 30 foreign and local investors who have signed
agreements with the Ethiopian government in prospecting,
exploration and produciton of mineral resources in the country
since the new proclamation was passed in 1994. Among them, 10 are
foreign investors. 
