<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Collects $8.6m for Displaced Ethiopians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia said Wednesday
that it has collected 61.5 million Birr (8.6 million U.S.
Dollars) from various sections of the society for rehabilitating
displaced Ethiopians by the Ethiopian-Eritrean war.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the National Fund Soliciting Committee of
Ethiopia was quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency as saying that
the total pledge to be collected does not include the fund to be
deducted in instalments from the salaries of those workers from
organizations of the federal government.
</P>
<P>
The committee said concerning material contribution,
governmental organizations and non-governmental organizations,
private institutions, individuals, U.N. agencies, Ethiopians
living abroad and foreign governments have donated consignments
of medicines, medical implements, tents, blankets, plastic
sheetings, canvases and clothings for the displaced people.
</P>
<P>
The committee once again urged Ethiopians to carry on with the
fund-raising for the rehabilitation of the war displaced and for the
construction of ravaged social institutions.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the number of displaced Ethiopians by the
war has reached 204,630. 
</P>
