<HEADLINE> Trilateral Commission Works Out Economic Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Russian trilateral
commission, which consists of representatives of the government
and both houses of parliament, has drafted the statement on
economic policy, according to the news reports of Itar-Tass news
agency Thursday.
</P>
<P>
First Deputy Speaker of the State Duma Vladimir Ryzhkov said
the members had drafted the final text of the statement on
Wednesday by midnight.
</P>
<P>
The commission agreed that economic approaches should be
largely altered, particularly with a vigorous customs policy to
protect the domestic market, Ryzhkov said.
</P>
<P>
The need for new approaches to the regulation of the banking
system was emphasized, according to the first deputy speaker.
</P>
<P>
He said the property of those banks that fail to meet
obligations to depositors may be siezed by the state.
</P>
<P>
Ryzhkov noted that if the statement passed, it would be fully
worked out by the end of the day and referred to the president,
acting prime minister and speakers of the Federation Council and
the State Duma.
</P>
<P>
According to the coordinator, the commission will submit on
Friday a Duma version of the document with a protocol to a meeting
of the State Duma Council. The protocol records differences
between factions on this document.
</P>
<P>
However, another report said, the president's office
responded negatively to the document drafted by the tripartite
commission.
</P>
<P>
Oleg Morozov, the commission's coordinator from the State Duma
and leader of the parliamentary group Russian Region, said
Thursday that in response, the president's staff sent its own
version of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The version consists of a preamble and one item, listing laws
which should be adopted, in the opinion of the president's office,
Morozov said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that "this completely changes the philosophy of
the political agreement".
</P>
<P>
The commission continued simultaneously working with the
president's office and the Federation Council (upper house),
Morozov said.
</P>
<P>
The statement on social and economic policy drafted by the
trilateral commission is one of the two important documents that
are to be worked out by the trilateral commission. The other one
is the political statement on the interaction of branches of
power, which is being drafted.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma would not confirm the nomination of Viktor
Chernomyrdin as prime minister before the two documents were
passed, some opposition leaders said in the parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
