<HEADLINE> Flood Crests On Major Chinese Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Millions of civilians and
soldiers are keeping watch as the floods peaks move on the Yangtze
River in central China and Songhua River in the northeast.
</P>
<P>
The most recent, the seventh flood crest on the Yangtze has not
caused any major problems even though water levels remain high
from Shishou in Hubei Province to Jiujiang in eastern Jiangxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
Water levels on Dongting and Poyang lakes in those two
provinces are also receding.
</P>
<P>
The major flood peak on the Songhua has been passing through
Jiamusi city, in the northeastern part of Heilongjiang Province. On
Thursday at 2:00 p.m., the water level there was 80.34 meters, and
the flow rate, 16,200 cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The water level at Harbin, the capital of Heilongjiang, has
continued subsiding, to 120.47 meters on Thursday at 2:00 p.m.,
but was still above the all-time high by 0.42 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
