<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's Wholesale Trade Index Declines in 2nd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's overall domestic
and foreign wholesale trade indices declined by 10.5 and 13.5
percent respectively in the second quarter 1998 over the same
period of 1997, according to a survey released Thursday by the
Singapore Department of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Excluding petroleum, the above-said domestic and foreign
indices fell by 10.9 and 13.9 percent respectively, the survey
said.
</P>
<P>
The quarterly figures in comparison between 1998 and 1997
showed that the sharp decline in the domestic wholesale index was
partly attributed to the 31.1 percent fall in the wholesaling of
textiles, wearing apparel and personal effects, and a slump of
21.4 percent in the wholesaling of timber, paints and construction
materials.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, wholesale turnover of electronic and electrical
components and industrial machinery reduced by 20.0 percent while
that of petroleum and petroleum products slid by 9.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The figures also indicated that all the foreign wholesale
activities, except for the sales of food, beverages and tobacco
which grew by 25.4 percent, reported slowdown in business. The
hardest hit in the foreign wholesale trade was the wholesaling of
timber, paints and construction materials whose turnover dived by
44.8 percent compared with a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Also in the foreign wholesale trade, turnover of petroleum and
petroleum products declined by 12.9 percent and other wholesale
activities that reported negative growth were general wholesale
trade (-13.0 percent), electronic and electrical components and
industrial machinery (-7.5 percent), and household equipment and
furniture (-3.6 percent).
</P>
<P>
The wholesale trade index measures the sales transactions of
wholesale establishment in the economy.
</P>
<P>
The survey noted that data for the compilation of the wholesale
trade indices are sourced from some 750 wholesale establishments
covered in the quarterly survey of wholesale trade and business
expectations surveys.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
