<HEADLINE> Russian Acting PM Calls for Government of Professionals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian Acting Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin on Wednesday called for a new cabinet formed
by professionals regardless of their party affiliations.
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old Chernomyrdin aired the idea on television in
the wake of a Crimean summit Wednesday with Ukraine President
Leonid Kuchma and Belarussian President Alexander Lukashenko.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said the cabinet members should be well aware of
their responsibility at a critical moment, Interfax-Ukraine news
agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin was reinstated by Russian President Boris Yeltsin
on August 23 after the sudden dismissal of the entire cabinet
headed by 35-year-old Sergei Kiriyenko amid financial and economic
turmoil in the country.
</P>
<P>
The crisis came to a head last week when Moscow declared it was
defaulting on some of the international debts and made a de facto
devaluation on the ruble.
</P>
<P>
The most important task was to make united efforts nationwide
in seeking way to come through the financial crisis, Chernomyrdin
said.
</P>
<P>
The first priority was to deal with shortage of funds and keep
the banking system in order, he said.
</P>
<P>
To overcome the crisis needed close cooperation with
neighboring countries, Chernomyrdin added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
