<HEADLINE> Doping Bans for Russian Swimmers Upheld </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The two-year bans on three
Russian swimmers for doping violation by the international
swimming body FINA have been upheld by the Court of Arbitration
for Sport (CAS) in Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Vladmir Pychnenko, Natalia Mechtcheriakova and Olga
Kotchetkova had been suspended by FINA's Doping Panel in
December, 1997 but the trio went to the CAS for arbitration.
</P>
<P>
CAS arbitrators Raymond Swert of Belgium, Swiss Denis Oswald
and Jean Gay decided to dimiss the appeal by the swimmers and
confirm the FINA sanctions, the CAS said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The CAS said the suspension of the trio, who tested positive
for metandienone, will end on October 18, 1999.  
</P>
