<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Japanese Economic Association Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting with Imai Takashi, honorary president of the Japan-China
Economic Association here today, said the the courage of millions
of Chinese in fighting the battle against flooding exhibits once
again the cohesiveness of the Chinese in difficult situations and
proves that the Chinese nation is indomitable.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed appreciation for the efforts of the Japan-China
Economic Association to increase mutual understanding and economic
and trade cooperation between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Although the Asian financial crisis has affected China's
economic growth, Jiang said, the Chinese government has adopted a
responsible attitude and, as a result, has paid the price for
keeping the Chinese currency stable.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that Japan will make its own effort to help
stabilize the region's economy by using its economic strength.
</P>
<P>
This year is the 20th anniversary of the Sino-Japanese peace
and friendship treaty, he said, and it is worth
commemorating. Since bilateral relations are at an important stage
between past and future, China and Japan should develop friendly
and cooperative relations geared for the 21st century, based on
the principles of the Sino-Japanese joint statement and
Sino-Japanese peace and friendship treaty, promoting friendship
for future generations.
</P>
<P>
Takashi expressed his admiration for China's flood control and
disaster relief work and its contribution to mitigating the
effects of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He also discussed proposals of the Japan-China Economic
Association on reciprocal cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Takashi told Jiang that the Japanese government and people hope
for jiang to pay a visit to Japan at his convenience.  
</P>
