<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods In Tibet Kill 53 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 53 people have been
killed in heavy floods and mudslides in the Tibet Autonomous
Region since mid-June, according to the latest official reports.
</P>
<P>
In the last two months, the floods have pushed water levels of
the Yarlung Zangbo and Lhasa rivers up to record levels. Of more
than 70 counties in the autonomous region, 40 have been affected.
</P>
<P>
Floodwaters have affected more than 80,000 local people, killed
over 4,000 head of livestock, inundated 13,333 ha. of farmland,
and destroyed over 2,000 houses.
</P>
<P>
Some 100,000 civilians and soldiers have been working to
fortify dikes, fill breaks in dikes, and evacuate flood victims.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have allocated at least 41 million yuan and
large amounts of materiel for the relief work.
</P>
<P>
The central government has expressed concern about the flood
situation there. Premier Zhu Rongji recently told central
government departments to give priority to floods in the region
and to help solve Tibet's problems in its fight with the
floods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
