<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 6.6 on
the Richter scale hit the western part of the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region in northwestern China today, according to the
country's earthquake monitoring service.
</P>
<P>
The quake occurred at 17:03 hours (Beijing Time) in Jiashi
County.
</P>
<P>
Tremors were felt by residents of Kashi Prefecture and the
Kizilsu Kirgis Autonomous Prefecture.
</P>
