<HEADLINE> China Guarantees Food, Clothing, Shelter For Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Victims of the worst floods in
China since 1954 will be provided with adequate food, clothing,
and places to live, Minister of Civil Affairs Doje Cering told
Xinhua today in an exclusive interview.
</P>
<P>
The minister has just returned from a visit to flood-ravaged
areas, and said the ministry will take further steps to see to it
that there are 0.5 kilograms of grain for each of the flood
victims, clothing to protect them from the cold, and adequate
housing.
</P>
<P>
Those who have become ill or who have been injured will receive
proper treatment, he said, to prevent the outbreak of epidemics.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has sent over 100 work teams and allocated over 3
billion yuan in funds and large quantities of relief goods for the
flood-damaged provinces. 
</P>
