support the ruble, allowing the currency to plunge. The central
bank also canceled dollar trading on the Moscow currency exchange.
Credit Suisse and its First Boston unit said profits were hit by
Russia's economic woes. Moscow's moves roiled world markets, and
U.S. stocks fell 79.30 points to 8523.35.
</P>
