<HEADLINE> China-Japan Peace, Friendship Treaty Reception </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Japanese gathered at
a reception here today to mark the 20th anniversary of the signing
of the China-Japan Peace and Friendship Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The reception was sponsored by the China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT) and the Japan-China
Association on Economy and Trade (JCAET).
</P>
<P>
CCPIT President Yu Xiaosong told those present that
non-governmental exchanges and cooperation have provided a strong
impetus for Sino-Japanese friendship. People-to-people contacts
and economic and trade cooperation between China and Japan have
been and will always be a major driving force behind the
development of bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sustained and sound development of Sino-Japanese economic and
trade ties will benefit economic development in China and
contribute to Japan's economic recovery and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sugichiro Watari, president of JCAET, said that the Japan-China
Peace and Friendship Treaty has laid a foundation for
good-neighborly relations.
</P>
<P>
In the spirit of the treaty, Japan and China have had
cooperation based on equality and mutual benefit and have learned
from each other to offset each other's deficiencies, and the two
nations will certainly contribute to peace and development in Asia
and in the world at large and usher in a promising new century.
</P>
