<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The number of real estate
transactions in Macao rose slightly in the first half of this year
over a year ago, but the contractual volume dropped considerably,
the Macao government said.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, a total of 6,683 real estate transactions
were made, up by 1.6 percent over the first half of last year,
according to figures released by the Census and Statistics
Department Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, the contracted amount was 4.3 billion patacas (about
537.5 million U.S. dollars), slumping by 56.9 percent, the figures
showed. 
