<HEADLINE> Athletics World Cup to Be Renamed Nelson Mandela Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 27 (Xinhua) - The athletics World Cup will be
renamed the Nelson Mandela Trophy for future editions of the
four-yearly continental team event, the International Amateur
Athletic Federation (IAAF) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The eighth World Cup will be staged in Johannesburg from
September 11-13.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the IAAF on Thursday, IAAF
president Primo Nebiolo said Mandela was an "inspirational
figure".
</P>
<P>
"We are honored that the World Cup trophies will now be named
after him," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The IAAF World Cup is a special athletics competition because
the team is more important than the individual. The event
represents unity and friendship between different parts of the
world and no individual personifies the quest for unity better
than Nelson Mandela," said the president.
</P>
<P>
In an attached letter to the statement, Mandela said, "I
accept this extraordinary gesture not as a tribute to me but to
all athletes and especially to those in Africa who have inspired
the world with their legendary achievements despite their
underprivileged beginnings," he said.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF will offer cash awards to athletes for the first time
at the World Cup -- 50,000 U.S. dollars for first place (60,000
U.S. dollars for relays), 20,000 for second and 10,000 for
third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
