<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Head Of Austrian Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, in a meeting today with
Alfred Gerstl, President of the Federal Council of the Austrian
Parliament, said he hopes that the Chinese National Peoples'
Congress (NPC) and the Austrian parliament will develop relations
further.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, expressed
his appreciation for Gerstl's efforts at promoting Sino-Austrian
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Gerstl said that he visited China's Guizhou Province and other
places and was deeply impressed by the national unity and dynamic
development.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed concern about the severe flooding in China
and sympathy for the people in the disaster-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Li told Gerstl that the fight against the flooding is still
going on but said he is confident that China will be triumphant
under the leadership of the Communist Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core. 
</P>
