<HEADLINE> China's Tallest Building In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's tallest
building, the 88-story Jinmao Mansion, was completed recently in
the Pudong new area in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The building in the center of the Pudong Financial and Trade
Development Zone covers 23,000 square meters of ground, and has
290,000 square meters of floor space.
</P>
<P>
The 420.5-meter tall building cost 540 million U.S. dollars. It
is the third tallest building in the world, after the Petronas
Twin Towers of Malaysia and the Sears Tower in the United States.
