<HEADLINE> Turkey Calls for All Efforts to Solve Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Turkey Thursday called for all
kinds of efforts to solve the conflict in the separatist Yugoslav
province of Kosovo so to prevent a wave of refugees.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, Turkish Foreign Ministry expressed
Ankara' concern about the Kosovo crisis, which it said has reached
a serious dimension threatening the peace and stability in the
Balkans and the Europe as a whole.
</P>
<P>
The statement deplored it as "a humanitarian tragedy in the
region" that the warring sides in Kosovo preferred to solve the
crisis by use of force rather than negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem has sent letters to his
counterparts of the southern European countries, underlining the
importance of providing assistance to Kosovo refugees whose number
has reached 200,000.
</P>
<P>
Cem also brought the project of the "Southern European
Humanitarian Assistance Initiative for Kosovonian Refugees" to the
attention of his counterparts in the region.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that the Turkish Red Crescent would send
humanitarian aid not only to Albania, but also to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has deep-rooted historical, humanitarian and cultural
ties with Kosovo, where a considerable number of Turks are still
living.
</P>
<P>
Since February, fierce fighting has erupted between the
Serbian forces and ethnic Albanian guerrillas who demand
independence from Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
