<HEADLINE> HK Ready for Smooth Changeover of Bus Franchise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The overwhelming majority of
franchised bus routes on the Hong Kong Island will be operated as
usual on September 1 despite a changeover of franchise, a
government official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
New World First Bus (NWFB), a newly organized bus company, will
replace China Motor Bus (CMB) to run franchised bus routes on the
Hong Kong Island starting from midnight of August 31.
</P>
<P>
The new franchisee, together with two bus operators Citybus and
Kowloon Motor Bus (KMB), will take over about 100 franchised
routes now run by CMB.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commissioner for Transport Dorothy Chan told a press
conference Thursday: "There will be no major change in routings
and bus stop arrangements for over 90 percent of the routes."
</P>
<P>
NWFB will take over 90 routes, including 31 cross harbor bus
routes, Citybus will run 11 more routes, and KMB will add two
cross harbor routes.
</P>
<P>
Chan noted that public bus services after midnight of August 31
will not be disrupted. NWFB will start operating all its five
overnight bus routes from midnight onwards, she said.
</P>
<P>
The official stressed that the Transport Department will work
together with all concerned parties to ensure a smooth transition
and a satisfactory continuation of franchised bus services.
</P>
</TEXT>
