<HEADLINE> China's Technology Export Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,500 types of China's
transferable technology can now be seen on the Internet, on the
website the Online Technology Export Fair of China.
</P>
<P>
The items include machinery, chemicals, electronics, building
materials, aviation and space technology, bioengineering, and some
of the country's most advanced carrier rocket and agricultural
cloning technology.
</P>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, the minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), said at the opening ceremony today that this
was the first time for China to use E-business to show technology
for exports.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC began to release commodity information in early July on
"Chinamarket" on the Internet, and in a month it had attracted
more than 10 million visits.
</P>
<P>
Shi said he hopes to increase technology exports in this way.
</P>
<P>
The nation's technology business grew in the 1990's more than
40 percent per year on average, far greater than the growth of
general trade.
</P>
<P>
The Online Technology Export Fair can be reached at
www.techfair.com.cn, or though the official MOFTEC site,
www.moftec.gov.cn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
