<HEADLINE> hke082765 -SriLanka to Get More Compensation for Gulf War Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Commission
for Compensation (UNCC) will give the Sri Lankan government an
additional 48 million U.S. dollars as compensation for the workers
who lost jobs due to the 1990-91 Gulf War, official sources said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics maintained by the Sri Lankan Bureau of
Foreign Employment, about 90,000 workers returned from Kuwait to
Sri Lanka during the Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
After the war, the United Nations established a special
commission on compensation known as the UNCC, to pay an allowance
to those who were compelled to return.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka received three installments of 15.9 million dollars
in March 1997, 48.8 million dollars in December 1996, and 33
million dollars in April this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
