<HEADLINE> Vasco Beats Barcelona 2-1 to Lift Copa Libertadores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian soccer powerhouse Vasco
da Gama beat Barcelona of Ecuador 2-1 in Guayaquil, Ecuador, on
Wednesday to lift South America's Copa Libertadores for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
Vasco opened the scoring in the 24th minute through Luizao,
who trapped a pass before firing a low blast past the Barcelona
goaltender.
</P>
<P>
Donisete added another in the 46th minute, taking advantage of
a defence confusion before the Ecuadorean club's goal.
</P>
<P>
The Guayaquil club narrowed the margin in the 79 minutes when
Anthony de Avila headed in a pass from the corner.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's game was the second leg of the final. In the first
leg, Vasco won 2-0.
</P>
<P>
This was Barcelona's second Copa Libertadores final loss in
eight years after conceding the 1990 final to Olimpia of Paraguay
2-0 and 1-1.
</P>
<P>
Following are the lineups:
</P>
<P>
Barcelona: Francisco Cevallos, Raul Noriega, Jimmy Montanero,
Luis Gomez, Holger Quinonez, Fricson George, Marcelo Morales,
Hector Carabali, Anthony De Avila, Nicolas Asencio and Agustin
Delgado.
</P>
<P>
Vasco: Carlos Germano, Vagner, Odvan, Mauro Galvao, Felipe,
Luizinho, Nasa, Juninho (Vitor), Pedrinho (Ramon), Donizete and
Luizao (Alex) 
</P>
</TEXT>
