<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's State Banks Introduce Loan Schemes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan state banks have
introduced several loan schemes to encourage investments,
especially in self employment cases, an official press release
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The release said these banks have brought down the interest
rates under the instruction of President Chandrika Kumaratunga.
</P>
<P>
The president has advised four banks - Bank of Ceylon, the
National Savings Bank, People's Bank and the State Morigage and
Investment Bank - to implement their loan schemes with reduced
interest rates, to help the investors.
</P>
<P>
Investors in agriculture, industry and services are invited to
make full use of the benefits of these new lending rates. They are
advised to obtain the assistance of the branch managers, the
release said.
</P>
<P>
The release said that a special desk has been set up at the
Finance Ministry to sort out any problems faced by customers in
negotiating loans with the above-mentioned state banks. 
