<HEADLINE> India's Agriculture Exports Decline in 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- India's agriculture exports in
1997-98 are estimated to have declined mainly due to a drop in
food grain exports from 37,840 million rupees (995.79 million U.S.
dollars) to 24,800 million rupees (652.63 million dollars) in
value terms, official sources said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Though "Basmati" rice exports rose to 1.674 million tons as
against 1.247 million tons during the previous year, on the whole
there was a decline in exports of many of the farm products. One
of the areas which witnessed a drastic fall in exports was wheat
which fell from 700,000 tons to very negligible levels.
</P>
<P>
Oil meals exports fell from 3.495 million tons to 3.403 million
tons. Processed vegetables fell from 116,000 tons to 109,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
As a percentage of the total exports, the share of farm product
exports fell to 15.87 percent in 1997-98 from previous year's
17.96 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
