<HEADLINE> Shares Prices Tumble on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices tumbled in light
dealings on the Singapore Stock Market Thursday as concerns over
the Russian crisis and the bearish regional environment continue
overhang the market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Industrial Index (STII) lost 14.97
points to end at 910. 88 points, reversing the gains Wednesday and
plunging to a fresh 10-year low.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 151.34 million units valued at
249.89 million Singapore dollars (about 146.99 million U.S.
dollars). Losers outstripped gainers by 208 to 81 with 300
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
SingTel remained the most active stock of the day as it closed
on a turnover of 20.86 million units. It was followed by ST Engg
that had 15.24 million stocks done. KepCorp was next with 8.17
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Robinson topped the gainers of the day as it gained 60 cents to
end at 4.80 Singapore dollars. SIA F edged up 40 cents to finish
at 7.55 Singapore dollars. SIA went up 30 cents to close at 5.30
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
as it lost 50 cents to 19.00 Singapore dollars. C &AMP; C shed 29
cents to finish at 2.89 Singapore dollars. MISC F inched down 20
cents to close at 1.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that investors picked up SPH and SingTel counters
on speculation these two stocks will have a higher weighting
Monday when a new benchmark index is introduced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
