<HEADLINE> Procurators to Crack Down on Embezzlement of Relief Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China's procuratorial offices
intend to intensify their efforts against the misappropriation of
donations in order to maintain stable social order in the
country's flood-ravaged areas.
</P>
<P>
Han Zhubin, procurator-general of the Supreme People's
Procuratorate, made this remark at a recent national working
conference.
</P>
<P>
While calling on procuratorial organs at all levels to make
greater contributions to the ongoing flood-fighting campaign, Han
ordered his subordinates to focus their attention on such illicit
activities as robbery, theft, disruption of disaster-relief
facilities, embezzlement of donations, and hoarding and
profiteering.
</P>
<P>
According to China's Criminal Law, the above
activities receive heavier punishments since they have
a serious negative impact on disaster-relief work and on the
society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
