<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday as players were
inclined to sell amidst the negative growth in the country's gross
domestic product (GDP) in the second quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index lost 10.32
points to 313.51, the all-share Emas Index dropped 2.40 points to
81.55, the Industrial Index dipped 13.09 points to 654.66 and the
Second Board Index eased 0.56 of a point to 77.58.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers by 402 to 128 while 148 counters
were unchanged, 242 counters were untraded and 37 counters
suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 102.917 million shares worth
134.628 million ringgit (about 32.092 million U.S. dollars) from
85.546 million shares valued at 118.912 million ringgit (about
28.346 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board volume was higher at 99.011 million shares worth
130.952 million ringgit (about 31.216 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 82.173 million shares valued at 115.399 million
ringgit (about 27.508 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover increased to 3.906 million shares
valued at 3.677 million ringgit (about 0.876 million U.S. dollars)
from 3.373 million shares worth 3.513 million ringgit (about 0.837
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off market transactions increased to 12.427 million shares
totaling 18.327 million ringgit (about 4.368 million U.S. dollars)
from 2.523 million shares worth 5.689 million ringgit (about 1.356
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday. 
</P>
