<HEADLINE> China to Further Cooperation With South Pacific Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China will further develop
its cooperation with the South Pacific Forum (SPF) and the
countries in the region, a senior Chinese Foreign Ministry
official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi made the remarks
while meeting with the representatives from the SPF -- Cook
Islands Prime Minister Geoffrey Henry, Micronesian Foreign
Minister Epel Ilon, Fiji Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade
Berenado Wunibobo, Kiribati Minister of Environment and Natural
Resources Development Willie Tokataake and SPF Secretary-General
Noel Levi.
</P>
<P>
Yang is leading a delegation attending the dialogue meeting on
August 26-27 after the 29th SPF summit.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also talked about international issues, trade,
fishery and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Micronesian President Jacob Nena on
Wednesday, Yang said that China is satisfied with the One-China
policy pursued by the Micronesian government and will push the
bilateral relations to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Yang also met Kiribati President Teburoro Tito, Palau President
Kuniwo Nakamura and foreign ministers from Fiji, Marshall Islands
and Vanuatu.
</P>
<P>
The SPF held a summit meeting in Pohnpei, Micronesia, on August
21-28 under the theme "From Reform to Growth: The Private Sector
and Investment as Keys to Prosperity." 
</P>
</TEXT>
