<HEADLINE> Minsheng Bank Improves Service For Taiwan Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of Minsheng
Bank is striving to improve service in a bid to help with the
financing of Taiwan investors in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1995, Minsheng Bank with headquarters based in
Beijing was China's first shareholding bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank has decided to provide services for Taiwan investors
in issuing floating fund loans, trade financing, honoring and
discounting bills and drafts, and issuing letters of credit.
</P>
<P>
The bank proposes to set up a regular information exchange
channel and launch a mutual guarantee fund as part of its efforts
to assist Taiwan investors.
</P>
<P>
These policies were announced recently during a meeting held
here by Minsheng Bank and the Taiwan-Invested Enterprises
Association of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 Taiwan-invested companies have so far been set
up in Shanghai, and some 500 of them have joined the association.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
