<HEADLINE> Afghans Stage Demonstrations Against US Missile Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Afghans staged
demonstrations against the U.S. missile attack on Afghanistan in
front of the U.S. Embassy in Kabul and U.N. office in the
provincial capitals of the country.
</P>
<P>
The protesters condemned the U.S. attack and termed it as "a
violation of all the internationally recognized norms and
principles," a report by Radio Kabul said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators chanted anti-U.S. slogans and burnt the U.S.
flags.
</P>
<P>
They asked the international community, particularly the
Islamic states to unanimously denounce the U.S. attack on alleged
terrorist networks in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. launched missile attack at Afghanistan on August 20 in
a bid to eliminate the alleged terrorist bases run by Saudi Osama
bin Laden. The missile attack resulted in loss of lives of at
least 30 people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
