<HEADLINE> Another Assassin of Former Chief Prosecutor Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Another assassin of the former
Iranian chief prosecutor Assadollah Lajevardi has been arrested,
the officials Iranian News Agency IRNA reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The assassin, whose name was not revealed, was arrested while
attempting to cross the border into Iraq, the IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
He also came from the outlawed Mujaheddin Khalq Organization
(MKO), which has claimed responsibility for the last Sunday's
shooting of Lajevardi, former head of the Prisons Organization.
</P>
<P>
The MKO member escaped the scene after shooting dead Lajevardi
at his shop in Tehran grand bazaar, but his accomplice Ali Akbar
Akbar Dehbalai was arrested by the police after being
wounded.
</P>
<P>
Dehbalai late died of his wounds Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The MKO is one of the major political groups which toppled the
former Iranian Shah regime in 1979, but it was outlawed in 1981
due to sharp differences with the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
During the past years, the MKO launched a series of attacks on
Iranian interests inside and outside the country.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation, the Iranian air force has carried out several
air raids on the MKO bases inside Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
