<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Companies Producing Biological Pharmaceuticals in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 26 (Xinhua) -- More and more Chinese investors
are trying their luck by investing in applied biological
engineering technology for the production of pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 200 biological pharmaceutical companies
across the country, of which 24 are listed on the stock markets,
according to a recent symposium on the industrial use of genetic
technology.
</P>
<P>
Last year, only two of these companies had sales exceeding 100
million yuan (12 million US dollars), and most of them did a
limited business, with sales ranging from a couple of million yuan
to several tens of millions.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the combined sales of all Chinese
bio-pharmaceutical producers in the past year was less than the
annual output value generated by one similar medium-size company
in the United States or Japan.
</P>
<P>
Ke Chuankui, general manager of the Jiuyuan Genetic Engineering
Co. Ltd. based in Hangzhou, the capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province, said, "this shows China, as a country with large genetic
resources, has great potential for the production and marketing of
genetic-engineering pharmaceuticals."
</P>
<P>
The industrial use of bio-engineering technology is widely
valued in different localities around the country. All of China's
existing 52 state-level high-tech industrial development zones
have listed the industrial use of bio-engineering technology as a
major project for accelerated development.
</P>
<P>
As the Chinese government provides preferential policies to
encourage the industrial use of bio-engineering technology, a
large number of traditional chemical pharmaceutical makers have
increased investment in the research, clinical testings and
processing of genetic medicines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980827.0158 </DOCNO>
