<HEADLINE> Russia, Vietnam to Enhance Scientific Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Vietnam are satisfied
with their cooperation in science and technology over the last few
years and determined to further the cooperation, the Itar-Tass
news agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A subcommission of the commission for trade and economic,
scientific and technological cooperation between the two countries
met here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed an agreement on establishing in Vietnam a
science center for carbonic materials.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed on further cooperation within the framework
of the joint tropical center set up in Vietnam with Russia's
assistance.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the center is the only interdepartmental
scientific organization of Russia in the tropical zone which has
the possibility to carry out specific research work.
</P>
<P>
A Vietnamese delegation headed by President Tram Duc Luong
arrived in Moscow on Monday on an official visit. Russian
President Boris Yeltsin met with the Vietnamese counterpart on
Tuesday. 
</P>
