<HEADLINE> Fourth Bus Blast in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Another bus explosion took
place in Uganda Wednesday, at least one woman was injured.
</P>
<P>
The Kampala-bound bus was carrying 60 passengers on Kabale
road, some 22 kilometers from Mbarara town. The blast occurred at
about 5:30 p.m. local time, said a report reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Fire caused by the blast engulfed the lower section of the bus
and crushed the driving shaft. The panic-stricken passengers
scrambled out of the flaming bus in time to escape the sizzling
inferno.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion is under investigation, police said.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth bus in less than two days to be involved in
an explosion incident.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, bomb explosions occurred on three buses going to
different destinations, killing 30 people and injuring many
others.
</P>
<P>
The bombs are suspected to have been planted in Kampala
because all the three ill-fated buses allegedly traveled out of
the Baganda bus station in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued Wednesday, Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni strongly condemned the terrorist attacks and vowed to
use every means to bring the perpetrators to book. 
</P>
</TEXT>
