<HEADLINE> Consultations on Selection Committee for First Macao SAR Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Work Group of Administrative
Affairs, a subsidiary of the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee, is
scheduled to conduct consultations from September 3-6 in Macao on
detailed plans for the founding of the Selection Committee for the
First Macao SAR Government.
</P>
<P>
The primary work of the selection committee, all of whose
members are permanent Macao residents, is to help choose the first
chief executive of the Macao SAR Government by consulting local
residents or nominating candidates for further election before
reporting the selected candidate to China's central government for
approval.
</P>
<P>
The consultation conferences will be attended by industrial and
commercial organizations, labor and religious groups, former
politicians, as well as those Macao residents who are also
deputies of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) and
members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the consultations, the Working Group of
Administrative Affairs will work out a detailed draft for the
establishment of the Selection Committee for the First Macao SAR
Government and, at an appropriate time, submit the draft to the
Plenary Session of the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee for further
deliberations and approval.  
</P>
</TEXT>
