<HEADLINE> Xinhua, Bernama Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua News Agency, the
state news agency of China, and Bernama, the national news agency
of Malaysia, signed here Thursday an agreement on cooperation in
marketing Xinhua news services in both English and Chinese in
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
With the signing of the agreement, Xinhua news services will be
made directly available to subscribers in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Zhang Guoliang, director of Asia
Pacific Region of Xinhua News Agency, and Syed Jamil Syed Jaafar,
acting general manager of Bernama on behalf of their respective
news agencies.
</P>
<P>
In his opening remarks on the occasion, Syed Jamil said that
the cooperation would see newspapers and publications especially
of the Chinese language and the Malaysian business community
benefiting from Xinhua's in-depth and comprehensive coverage of
China's mainland, Hong Kong, the surrounding regions and also the
world from an Asian perspective.
</P>
<P>
Syed Jamil said local companies with investments in China would
find Xinhua a reliable source of government, business and general
information which could be useful for making prudent investment
and business decisions.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guoliang introduced Xinhua News Agency on the occasion
and said "The people and organizations of countries and regions
are watching closely what happens in China and to meet their
needs, Xinhua, as the official news agency of China, can provide
comprehensive, accurate and authoritative news about China."
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that there is a big market in the Asia-Pacific
region for Xinhua news services as countries in the region have
maintained age-old friendly relations, close economic links and
frequent contacts with China.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua, established in 1931, at present transmits 1.5 million
words or characters in seven languages and 100 news photos daily
in over 130 countries and regions throughout the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
