<HEADLINE> Tel Aviv explosion Injures 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 12 people were
injured Thursday morning in an explosion in a busy street in Tel
Aviv, Israeli police said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion went off in a trash can at about 0850 local time
(0550 GMT) at a corner of the Allenby Street, which is one of the
busiest in Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
A bus carrying passengers just left the scene before the
exposion, otherwise, the explosion could have caused more injuries
or damage, the police added.
</P>
<P>
A pregnant woman and two children were among the injured, and
two of the injured were in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the bombing, Israeli police sealed off the
scene to conduct investigation into the incident.
</P>
<P>
No one has yet claimed responsibility for the explosion, but
the police suspected that it could be a terror attack. 
</P>
