<HEADLINE> Conspirators Arrested for Internet Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Law enforcement departments in
central China's Hunan Province recently cracked a case of fraud
involving use of the Internet.
</P>
<P>
In June this year, Liu Zheng and five co-conspirators listed
false information via the Internet in the name of Xing Yuan
Corp.. The conspirators defrauded a company in Shenzhen, south
China's Guangdong Province, of 150,000 fabric bags valued at
200,000 yuan (24,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The conspirators sold the bags to neighboring counties and
cities in need of flood relief materials, and have since
squandered over 90,000 yuan received as a result of the fraudulent
Internet transaction.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan Public Security Bureau investigated the case for some
20 days and arrested the six co-conspirators in early August.
</P>
