<HEADLINE> Second Tiger Cup Starts in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia beat Singapore 2-0 while
Vietnam nipped the Laos 4-1 in the opening day of the
second southeast Asian Soccer Tournament, the Tiger Cup '98, here
today.
</P>
<P>
Eight teams from Malaysia, Singapore, Laos, Indonesia, the
Philippines, Thailand, Myanmar and Vietnam will play 16 matches
in two groups at the Hanoi stadium and Ho Chi Minh city's Thong
Nhat (Unification) stadium.
</P>
<P>
The biannual Tiger Cup is southeast Asia's biggest soccer
tournament and the largest international tournament of its kind
ever to be hosted by Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The Tiger Cup was originally scheduled to be held in Indonesia
before social and economic upheavals in that country forced
organizers to look elsewhere for a host.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia, which had originally offered to stand in as late
replacement for Indonesia, decided not to host it because it was
too busy preparing for next month's Commonwealth Games.
</P>
<P>
The Tiger Cup is scheduled to conclude on September 5. 
</P>
