<HEADLINE> Former NBA Legends Team up to Face China's National Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Former National Basketball
Association (NBA) All-Star players Alex English and Adrian
Dantley are teaming up to become a lethal scoring unit against
the Chinese national team in October during the four-game
American Legends of Basketball Tour of China.
</P>
<P>
In NBA regular season and playoff games, the duo scored more
than 50,000 points. English scored most of his 25,613 points with
the Denver Nuggets. Most of Dantley's 23,177 NBA points were
scored while playing for the Utah jazz, Detroit Pistons, LA
Lakers., Dallas Mavericks and Milwaukee Bucks.
</P>
<P>
English has 1,661 playoff points and Dantley got 1,558 in the
post-season.
</P>
<P>
Coached by Wang Fei, China will try to beat the former-NBA
players with a team made up of seven players who saw action in
the Asian Basketball Confederation Championships in Saudi Arabia
last year, where it placed third after being upset by the
eventual champion South Korea in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhizhi and Sun Jun will be joined by veterans Gong Xia
obin, Liu Yudong, Hu Weidong, Zhang Jinsong, Li Xiaoyong and
forward Li Nan. The others are Goodwill Games veteran and
Mongolian Bateer, guard Liu Qiang and Ding Wei.
</P>
<P>
The Tour features four games in three cities. The former NBA
players will be coached by one of the sport's true legends --
Oscar "The Big O" Robertson. The Games are scheduled for October
16 and 18 in Shanghai, October 20 in Hefei and October 23 in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Joining English and Dantley will be Moses Malone, James
Worthy, Craig Hodges and Tom Chambers. The full team list will
be announced in September. 
</P>
