<HEADLINE> India, South Africa to Cooperate in Mining, Geology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 27 (Xinhua) -- India and South Africa have
decided to cooperate in mining and geological projects, official
sources said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two side so far have identified six projects including
geoscience mapping in the near-shore environment along the eastern
coastal margin for the purpose of identifying off-shore diamond
deposits, metallogenic map for India and South Africa, evaluation
of stability of underground mines, working through micro-seismic
techniques, hydro-fracturing for stress measurement and
characterization and processing of gold and diamond.
</P>
<P>
A protocol in this regard was signed during the visit of Indian
Steel and Mines Minister Naveen Patnaik to South Africa recently.
The signing of the protocol is the culmination of the agreement
for cooperation in the fields of geology and mineral resources,
which was signed in October last year during the Indian prime
minister's visit to that country. 
</P>
