<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia' Population Doubles in 36 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Preliminary results of
Cambodia's first census in 36 years shows that the country's
population hit 11.42 million as of March 3, 1998, doubling the 5.7
million figure in 1962.
</P>
<P>
According to data released on Tuesday by the Ministry of
Planning and the National Institute of Statistics, 5.59 million of
those counted are male and 5.97 million are female. The annual
growth rate is 2.44 percent.
</P>
<P>
The most populous province is Kampong Cham with 1.6 million
people, while Pailin is the least populated with only 23,000. The
average population density is 65 people per square kilometer.
</P>
<P>
The initial results also show that Cambodia's population could
reach 13 million by 2005 and 15 million by 2010.
</P>
<P>
It will present a challenge for the government to pursue a
policy that strikes a balance between population and economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
The final results of the census are due to be published in July
1999; it will provide some special data about health and education
issues as well as immigration patterns and living conditions.
</P>
</TEXT>
