<HEADLINE> Romanian Financial Market in Turmoil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Romania's stock market
experienced its worst turmoil Thursday partly because of the
impacts of the Russian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Share prices plummeted by more than 9 percentage points, the
biggest drop since the founding of Romania's stock market in the
early 1990s, the press here said.
</P>
<P>
The BET index, which is representative of Romania's 10 major
first-rate stocks, slipped to a record low of 348.41 points for
the first time to lose 9.28 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BET composite index slid to 487.86 points, a loss of 9.3
percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The index at the RASDAQ exchange, which is engaged in the sale
of medium and small enterprise stocks, finished 4.22 percent lower
at 809.87.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Romania's foreign exchange market fluctuated,
with the national currency, the leu, continuing to weaken. The
leu fell to below 9,000 to 1 against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Romanian economists say the bleak stock market is in part a
result of Russia's financial crisis and the ruble's devaluation.
However, the main cause is the country's unsatisfactory economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
Only after the government takes strong measures to stimulate
the economy and reform its macro-economic policies can the stock
and exchange markets reverse their decline, experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
