include exchange of quality strains, sending of Myanmar trainees
to research centers and universities in India and exchange of
delegations for the development of agricultural techniques and
investment, the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, the Indian minister visited Yangon,
reaching a memorandum of understanding with Myanmar on
technological cooperation in the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in March, India agreed to extend a loan of 10 million
U.S. dollars to Myanmar for carrying out projects in the rail
transportation and industry sectors in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
