<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Meets With Presidents of Ukraine, Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, Aguest 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian Acting Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin held talks with Presidents of Ukraine and
Belarus, Leonid Kuchma and Alexander Lukashenko, on Russian
financial crisis Wednesday in Crimea.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin briefed the presidents of the Russian financial
crisis and the measures taken by the government and the central
bank to stabilize the situation, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the talks he stressed that the three countries had to
coordinate actions to reduce the impact of the crisis on their
economies and trade because of their close economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said after a meeting with Kuchma, "it wasn't about
trying to reach decisions or agreements, but we simply had to
discuss and exchange advice," the agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma was quoted by the report as saying, "In Ukraine, we are
not any less worried than Russians about the situation on the
financial market, and we understand that sooner or later there
will be repercussions in Ukraine."
</P>
<P>
In Crimea, Chernomydin also met with IMF Managing Director
Michel Camdessus, discussing the financial situation worldwide and
in Russia. The measures Russia has taken to deal with the crisis
were also discussed, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A 22.6- billion-U.S.-dollar IMF-led bailout package approved in
July has so far failed to calm the country's economic maelstrom.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin arrived in Crimea Wednesday afternoon and was to
fly back to Moscow in the evening. 
</P>
