<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Develop Export Crops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
allocated 200 million rupees (3 million U.S. dollars) this year
for the development of export crops, according to Agriculture
Ministry sources here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the money has been distributed to producers of
export crops. The money would not be recovered and the producers
could use it to improve their output.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the steps taken by the Sri Lankan government for
the development of export crops, the sources said, adding that
assistance would also be provided to those who do not have their
own land to cultivate crops. Land would be given to them in
addition to the financial assistance granted to those engaged in
the production of export crops.
</P>
<P>
Some land owners who have neglected their lands will be given
an opportunity to cultivate them immediately or else their lands
would be taken away and distributed among others, the sources
stressed.  
