<HEADLINE> Private Party to Run 26 Airports in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Transport and
Communications Ministry will pick a private party to operate 26
airports which come under the jurisdiction of the Aviation
Department, Deputy Minister Pradit Pattaraprasit said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A winning bidder will have a concession to run all the airports
but their ownership will still belong to the department, Pradit
was quoted Thursday by The Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The contractor will pay a concession fee to the state and
employ the staff of the department, who are working at the
airports, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The private participation will improve the airport service and
help cut state budget currently spent on these airports
nationwide," he said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will not let private parties pick only profitable
airports because loss-ridden airports would otherwise be left with
the state, Pradit said.
</P>
<P>
"Actually, loss-ridden airports could make profits under
private management," he added. 
</P>
