<HEADLINE> Southern China's Villages to Promote Self-governing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 27 (Xinhua) -- All villages in rural
Guangdong province in southern China are expected to govern
themselves as a way of improving the rural grass-roots
administration.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to replace the current
administrative office with village committee as the leading body
of a village. The village committee members are to be elected
instead of appointed and the committee will have several villager
groups to oversee affairs in communities.
</P>
<P>
The practice will be tried out in several places in the second
half of this year, and be accompanied by a publicity campaign,
sources say. All villages will be electing their village committee
by the end of June next year.
</P>
<P>
Special emphasis will be put on keeping the elections open,
fair and democratic, in accordance with the law, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has said that the villages should
make sure that rural economic relations remain unchanged and that
farmers' rights and interests are not violated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
