<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Still Strong in Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Even though China's Hebei
province has been affected to a certain degree by the Southeast
Asian Financial Crisis, foreign trade of 21 development zones is
still good, according to a provincial government official.
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports of the zones amounted to 300 million
U.S. dollars during the first half of the year, up 16.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The official says that Hebei has been tried to ensure an
economic growth rate of 11 percent, and increasing exports is one
of the means.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period, Hebei's development zones were
involved in more than 1,150 overseas-funded projects, and used 2
billion U.S. dollars, a third of the province's total amount of
foreign investment. Twenty-one of the companies in these zones
have invested over 3 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
To increase foreign trade, the provincial government has
expanded to markets beyond East Asia, resulting in a 13 percent
increase in exports to the United States during the first six
months.  
</P>
