<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico, Germany Sign Investment Promotion Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and Germany signed an
investment protection and promotion agreement Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A press statement from the Department of Commerce and
Industrial Development (SAECOFI) said that the main purpose of
the document was to improve the investment environment in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The document will be sent to the Mexican Senate. If the
agreement is approved, both countries will be given the right to
restrict the flux of the capital related to investments, SAECOFI
said.
</P>
<P>
In Mexico there are 539 enterprises that have to do with German
investment. Germany is the third largest investor from Europe with
an investment of almost 1.305 billion U.S. dollars made during
1994-1997.
</P>
<P>
SAECOFI said the Mexican Senate has approved similar agreements
with Argentina, Spain and Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
