<HEADLINE> World Bank Aids Panama with 2 Million USD for Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank will
finance an education campaign in Panama with an investment of more
than 2 million U.S. dollars, said the Education Board Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used by the Panamanian authorities to buy and
distribute 260,000 books and teaching materials for 4,486 school
libraries across the country.
</P>
<P>
According to Education Minister Hector Penalba, this campaign
will benefit about 250,000 students in the poorest areas in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The Education Minister distributed materials to the Ernesto
T. Lefrevre school, which is located in a remote area in the
eastern part of Panama City.
</P>
<P>
"For the first time, these boys and girls will have -- in
addition to basic textbooks -- complementary materials such as
puzzles, games, globes and other learning tools," said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, which is a part of the modernization project of
the Panamanian Educational System, was started by President
Ernesto Perez Balladares who has always been an advocate for
equality in education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
