<HEADLINE> Indonesia Grants Visa Facility to Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
decided to grant visa facility to Chinese citizens for visits to
Indonesia, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese citizens wishing to come to Indonesia for business or
investment can now apply for a visa from Indonesian diplomatic
missions in any country, Justice Minister Muladi said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Such privilege can be enjoyed on the condition that the
applicant is already a member of the Chinese Chamber of Commerce
and Industry, Antara News Agency Thursday quoted the minister as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the same privilege will be given for group
tourist visits. "An Indonesian representative mission abroad could
issue a visa at its own initiative," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, Hong Kong SAR passport holders are allowed
to make a visa-free visit to Indonesia for 14 days. The privilege
is given on a reciprocal basis, Muladi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
