<HEADLINE> Brazil's Pork Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil exported 7,350
tons of pork in July, up 36.9 percent compared with the same month
last year, the Brazilian Association of Pork Producers said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, export earnings in the period grew by a marginal 0.85
percent because of drops in pork prices on the international
market.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months this year, the country's pork exports
increased by 19.84 percent in earnings and 42.52 percent in volume
in comparison with the same period in 1997, the association said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
