<HEADLINE> Beijing Issues Tougher Measures against Piracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A decree from Beijing's
Copyright Administration now prohibits people from carrying video
cameras in cinemas.
</P>
<P>
Video compact discs made from a copy shot in a local cinema
have become an growing part of the pirated VCD business, local
observers say, and more than 20 percent of the VCDs sold at local
market are found to be pirated products.
</P>
<P>
Liu Dongwei, vice director of the Copyright Administration,
says that the tougher measure is being enforced after a recent
legal case has been solved against infringement upon
copyrights. Earlier, 10 film studios brought a suit against the
Tiandu Copyright Agency, which had granted copyrights to dealers
without permission of the owners. The prosecutors won the case and
were compensated for.  
</P>
</TEXT>
