<HEADLINE> Romania Condemns Terrorist Blast in South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Foreign Minister
Andrei Plesu Wednesday condemned the bombing in a South African
restaurant aiming at the United States, saying that Bucharest is
firmly opposed to terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Plesu stressed that Romania is opposed to all acts of
terrorism, saying that his country is worried about the spate of
terrorist bombings which have been occurring one after the other
in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
A man was killed and 27 people were injured when a bomb
exploded at the "Planet Hollywood" restaurant in Cape Town Tuesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Among the wounded were five members of a British family of six,
including two children. The family arrived in Cape Town that day
on a holiday trip.
</P>
<P>
A man telephoned a Cape Town radio station the same night,
claiming a group named Muslims Against Global Oppression was
responsible for the blast.
</P>
<P>
The caller said the move was in retaliation for the
U.S. missile attacks on suspected terrorist camps in Afghanistan
and Sudan last week.
</P>
<P>
But a coordinator of the Muslim group Moain Achmad reportedly
denied the allegation Wednesday, saying someone was trying to
discredit his group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
