<HEADLINE> Gullit Set to Manage Newcastle United </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Former Dutch international Ruud
Gullit will fly in to Newcastle on Thursday to take over from
Kenny Dalglish as manager of Newcastle United.
</P>
<P>
According to the Daily Mirror which publishes Thursday, the
former Chelsea manager has been offered a
one-million-pound-a-season deal which would make him the
highest-paid club manager in the English Premiership.
</P>
<P>
The tabloid paper said that Newcastle directors traveled to
Amsterdam on Monday for secret talks with Gullit and they wanted
him to seal his move to St James' Park on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gullit was sacked by Chelsea earlier this year and Newcastle
have struggled to maintain the standards set under former manager
Kevin Keegan.
</P>
<P>
Dalglish's reign as Newcastle manager effectively ended after
the 1-1 draw at Chelsea on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact that the Premiership season is only two games
old, Dalglish has become the first managerial casualty of the
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another tabloid paper the Sun reported that Gullit
had been offered the job of manager of crisis Tottenham Hotspur,
taking over the job from Swiss coach Christian Gross. 
</P>
</TEXT>
