<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Benfica Moves into Group Stages of Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Two-time European Cup champions
Benfica advanced into the group stages of the European Champions
league on Wednesday despite losing their second qualifying round,
second leg match 4-2 away to Beitar Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Benfica's crushing 6-0 first leg victory in Lisbon secured
them a place in the league with a 8-4 win on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Nuno Gomes scored a 17th minute penalty and Joao Pinto scored
in the last minute for the 1961 and 1962 winners.
</P>
<P>
There were also goals galore for Spartak Moscow, who beat
Bulgarian side FC Liteks 6-2 at home for an 11-2 aggregate win.
Liteks' Veselin Ignatov was sent off in the 35th minute.
</P>
<P>
Two goals each from Andrei Tikhonov and Brazilian striker
Robson and further goals from Yegor Titov and Ilya Tsymbalar put
the Russians through.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile in Eindhoven, PSV Eindhoven escaped an early fright
to reach the Champions league against Maribor Teatanic with a 4-1
second leg win after extra time.
</P>
<P>
The Slovenians scored after only five minutes when PSV's
Brazilian center back Marcos slipped trying to clear the ball,
leaving Dalibor Filipovic clear to run through and add to their
2-1 home leg advantage.
</P>
<P>
PSV replied within three minutes when Ruud van Nistelrooy
headed home.
</P>
<P>
Maribor's Damjan Gajser could have made the tie safe for the
Slovenians but struck the post in the 62nd minute.
</P>
<P>
His miss enabled Arnold Bruggink to put the aggregate score
level at 3-3 in the 69th minute.
</P>
<P>
The draw finally turned in PSV's favour in the first phase of
extra time when a Dennis Rommedahl shot was fumbled by the
goalkeeper in the 100th minute and two minutes later Gilles de
Bilde struck in a fine effort from the edge of the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
In Lodz, Poland, Manchester United was managed to a 0-0 draw
against LKS Lodz in a dull game. With two goal advantage from
the first leg, Manchester United team secured a place in the
champions league.
</P>
<P>
In Belgrade, veteran Lothar Mattaeus scored with a
perfectly-judged curving free kick a minute before time to give
Bayern Munich a 1-1 draw with Yugoslavia's Obilic.
</P>
<P>
Bayern cruised through 5-1 on aggregate after winning the
first leg 4-0 in Munich.
</P>
<P>
Winners from the qualifying round will join pre-qualifiers
Lens, Juventus, Kaiserslautern, Barcelona, Ajax, Arsenal, Porto
and holders Real Madrid in Thursday's draw in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
The draw for six groups of four teams will be made at 1500GMT.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
