<HEADLINE> French Bags Two Golds at Track Cycing Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Arnaud Tournant won the kilometer
time trial title and Philippe Ermenault retained the pursuit
champion as French riders won both gold medals on offer on the
opening night of the world track cycling championships in Borde
aux, France, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tournant, 20, was credited with a time of one minute 01.879
second, the fastest recorded at sea level and an average speed of
58.178 kph.
</P>
<P>
Australian Shane Kelly, the defending champion, won the silver
medal and American Erin Hartwell took the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Ermenault beat his compatriot and close friend Francis Moreau
in the pursuit final as French riders finished 1-2.
</P>
<P>
Ermenault edged out Moreau by 84-100ths of a second to win in
a time of 4:20.627. Germany's Robert Bartko won the bronze medal
by beating Ukraine's Alexandre Simonenko. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
