<HEADLINE> Frenchman Wins Individual Pursuit in Cycling Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Philippe
Ermenault defeated Francis Moreau in the all-French final of the
men's individual pursuit event at the World Cycling Championships
in Bordeaux on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ermenault clocked 4 minutes, 20.627 seconds for the 4,000
meters, beating the 33-year-old Moreau by 0.839 second.
</P>
<P>
It was France's second gold medal of the night. Earlier Arnaud
Tournant won the kilometer time trial by beating three-time
champion Shane Kelly of Australia. 
</P>
