<HEADLINE> World Record Holder Gebrselassie to Miss Word Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 26 (Xinhua) -- World record holder of
5,000 and 10,000 meters Haile Gebrselassie of Ethiopia will not
compete in the upcoming World Cup to be held here on September
11-13.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian did not attend last week's African championships
in Dakar, Senegal, and so was not considered for the African
squad.
</P>
<P>
Despite his absence, the African line-up, named on Wednesday,
still boasts four world record holders, six world champions and
an Olympic champion.
