<HEADLINE> Benfica Moves into Group Stages of Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 26 (Xinhua) -- Two-time European Cup champions
Benfica advanced into the group stages of the European Champions
league on Wednesday despite losing their second qualifying round,
second leg match 4-2 away to Beitar Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Benfica's crushing 6-0 first leg victory in Lisbon secured
them a place in the league with a 8-4 win on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Nuno Gomes scored a 17th minute penalty and Joao Pinto scored
in the last minute for the 1961 and 1962 winners.
</P>
<P>
There were also goals galore for Spartak Moscow, who beat
Bulgarian side FC Liteks 6-2 at home for an 11-2 aggregate win.
Liteks' Veselin Ignatov was sent off in the 35th minute.
</P>
<P>
Two goals each from Andrei Tikhonov and Brazilian striker
Robson and further goals from Yegor Titov and Ilya Tsymbalar put
the Russians through.
</P>
<P>
Spartak and Benfica join pre-qualifiers Lens, Juventus,
Kaiserslautern, Barcelona, Ajax, Arsenal, Porto and holders Real
Madrid in Thursday's draw in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
The draw for six groups of four teams will be made at 1500GMT.
</P>
</TEXT>
